The final Federal IT Modernization Report has been delivered, as part of the Trump Administration's efforts to modernize Federal IT. The report outlines actions to be taken to modernize citizen-facing services by implementing a more secure, agile, and cost-effective infrastructure, with the help of shared services. The report was developed through an open and transparent process, gathering feedback from industry experts. Over 100 companies and individuals submitted comments during the public comment period, which influenced changes made to the report. The report's action plan will begin on January 1, 2018. The feedback received affirmed the importance of Federal IT modernization and validated the proposed approach. The authors express gratitude for industry engagement and emphasize the ongoing need for industry participation as agencies accelerate their modernization activities.